During a press briefing, Mayor Mitch Landrieu discussed the progress of the infrastructure projects that are being implemented under the Biden administration. He highlighted the importance of investing in infrastructure and the positive impact it has on job creation, economic growth, and the overall well-being of communities. He also emphasized the need for access to clean air, safe water, high-speed internet, and clean energy. Mayor Landrieu mentioned several ongoing infrastructure projects across the country and highlighted the administration's commitment to completing them on time and within budget. He also expressed concern about the potential negative consequences of a default on the national debt and urged Congress to take action to avoid it.